entry.title: Storm System Kills at Least 26 People Across Central U.S.
entry.content: Fueled by a series of rotating thunderstorms, the system felled trees and power lines and battered homes across at least eight states.

entry.title: Deadly Shipwreck Shakes Italy's Anti-Immigration Government
entry.content: The number of refugees and other migrants crossing the Mediterranean Sea to reach Europe is rising—and tragedies are increasing.

entry.title: America Has Too Much Parking. Really.
entry.content: Many cities are getting rid of spaces, freeing land for new development. “People are looking for a place to live, not to park,” said a Buffalo city official.
